article:
'Mast/stem cell growth factor receptor' (SCFR), also known as 'proto-oncogene
c-Kit' or 'tyrosine-protein kinase Kit' or 'CD117,' is a protein that in humans
is encoded by the 'KIT' gene. Multiple transcript
variants encoding different isoforms have been found for this gene. KIT was first described by the German biochemist Axel
Ullrich in 1987 as the cellular homolog of the feline sarcoma viral oncogene v-
kit.
